<revisionlist>
  <revision rev="1" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>1c350339229b281c8b200cdd2178da02</srcmd5>
    <version>0.4.11</version>
    <time>1763476771</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>This package provides the Linux kernel driver for Xbox One and Xbox Series X|S accessories.
it serves as a modern replacement for xpad, aiming to be
compatible with Microsoft's Game Input Protocol (GIP).

Now that xone-dongle-firmware is also in Factory, the driver can easily be installed and used on openSUSE :)</comment>
    <requestid>1318347</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="2" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>997aeeaa3b55eec1f029265a1829d05f</srcmd5>
    <version>0.5.4</version>
    <time>1769979841</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- Update to release 0.5.4
  * Work around another sleeping issue
- Update to release 0.5.3
  * Work around sleeping issues
- Update to release 0.5.2
  * Add fw override module parameter
- Update to release 0.5.1
  * Fix pairing through sysfs
- Update to release 0.5.0
  * This version breaks compatibility with kernels older than 6.5.0 
    to lessen the maintainership burden.
  * Increase the dongle pairing timout
  * Support firmwares for all the defined dongles
  * Merge mainline changes from medusalix
- Update to release 0.4.12
  * Fix leftover autosuspend handling
  * Reduce the sleep before registering a GIP client
  * Cleanup a warning
  * Improve module unloading for testing

Requires: https://build.opensuse.org/requests/1330200</comment>
    <requestid>1330202</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="3" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>e32ddd0e7024676a593ed875c0832b03</srcmd5>
    <version>0.5.5</version>
    <time>1771243754</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- Update to release 0.5.5
  * Add sysfs interface to power off wireless controllers 

I also made the version dependencies a bit stricter. xone now requires the kernel module in the same version. xone-dongle-firmware needs to be in the new version format introduced with the latest version which zypper unfortunately recognizes as lower version and doesn't want to update to. So I enforce a &quot;lower&quot; version for now.</comment>
    <requestid>1333055</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="4" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>5e649ca4ebdb20c6c63c33f48e80955a</srcmd5>
    <version>0.5.7</version>
    <time>1773581553</time>
    <user>dimstar_suse</user>
    <comment>- Update to release 0.5.7
  * dongle, mt76: fix cold/warm firmware init and enable automatic controller reconnection
  * Change timeout_secs to milliseconds for pairing work
  * Simplify firmware loading cancellation logic
- Update to release 0.5.6
  * Add more info to the active_clients sysfs
  * Fix small dongle pairing - add pairing scan channel rotation and diagnostics
  * Add sleep before firmware reset</comment>
    <requestid>1339041</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="5" vrev="1">
